comments.raw_text:
@beltzner: again, my point is that this speaks directly to Mozilla's mission. It should trump the desire to streamline the menus.

Also, I think in this case, Hicks law works in my argument's favour. If a person who doesn't know the web is malleable must first choose to consider whether or not they are a web developer (or curious about this), then the odds of them revealing the source of the page diminish.

@kev: You already know you want to view the source of a page, so right-click>view source works for you.  This bug is about moving view source from a developer-centric placement to one that all users can find.

